  "prompt": "What are the rules for Yahoo's fantasy hockey?",
  "response": "Yahoo Fantasy Hockey is a popular platform for managing fantasy hockey leagues. The rules can vary depending on the league settings, but here are the general rules and structure:\n\n### 1. **League Types**\n   - **Public Leagues**: Open to all users, with default settings.\n   - **Private Leagues**: Created by users, customizable settings.\n\n### 2. **League Formats**\n   - **Head-to-Head**: Compete against a different opponent each week. Win categories to earn points.\n   - **Rotisserie (Roto)**: Accumulate stats over the season, ranked in each category.\n   - **Points Only**: Players earn points based on their real-life performance, and total points determine standings.\n\n### 3. **Roster Positions**\n   - Typically includes:\n     - 2 Centers (C)\n     - 2 Left Wingers (LW)\n     - 2 Right Wingers (RW)\n     - 4 Defensemen (D)\n     - 2 Goalies (G)\n     - 4 Bench (BN) spots\n     - Injured Reserve (IR) spots for injured players\n\n### 4. **Scoring Categories**\n   - **Skaters**: Goals (G), Assists (A), Plus/Minus (+/-), Penalty Minutes (PIM), Power Play Points (PPP), Shotted on Goal (SOG), Hits (HIT), Blocks (BLK)\n   - **Goalies**: Wins (W), Goals Against Average (GAA), Save Percentage (SV%), Shutouts (SHO)\n\n### 5. **Draft**\n   - **Snake Draft**: Order reverses each round.\n   - **Auction Draft**: Players bid on players with a budget.\n\n### 6. **Transactions**\n   - **Add/Drop**: Add free agents or drop players from your roster.\n   - **Trades**: Trade players with other teams, subject to league approval.\n   - **Waivers**: Players not immediately available can be claimed on waivers.\n\n### 7. **Playoffs**\n   - Typically occur in the last few weeks of the NHL season.\n   - In Head-to-Head leagues, top teams advance to a playoff bracket.\n\n### 8. **Prizes**\n   - Public leagues often have Yahoo-sponsored prizes.\n   - Private leagues can set their own prizes.\n\n### 9. **Customization**\n   - League managers can customize many settings, including roster size, scoring categories, playoff structure, and trade rules.\n\n### 10. **Access**\n   - Manage your team via the Yahoo Fantasy Sports website or mobile app.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, always refer to the official Yahoo Fantasy Hockey guide or your specific league settings.",
